pullRequest.body:
We prove that in a nonarchimedean ring, $$\sum_{(i, j) \in I \times J} a_i b_j = \left(\sum_{i \in I} a_i \right)\left(\sum_{j \in J} b_j\right),$$ provided that both sums on the right-hand side converge unconditionally.

---
